  <T n="name">0x965E861E<!--Horse Purchasing, Rescuing, & Selling--></T>
  <L n="slides">
    <U>
      <T n="image" p="InEP14\UI\Lessons\EP14_HorseBuyRescueSell_Slide1.png">2f7d0004:00000000:dd7cd6c2785f3f15</T>
      <T n="text">0xA76E2495<!--If you don't start off with a Horse in your Household right out of Create a Sim, there are a variety of ways to acquire a Horse! Two of the main ways are to <b>Purchase</b> or <b>Rescue</b>. You can also <b>Breed</b> Horses. To learn more about <b>Breeding Horses</b> visit the <b>Horse Breeding Lesson</b>.\n\nIt is also possible to <b>Sell</b> a Horse for Simoleons.--></T>
    </U>
    <U>
      <T n="image" p="InEP14\UI\Lessons\EP14_HorseBuyRescueSell_Slide2.png">2f7d0004:00000000:dd7cd6c2785f3f16</T>
      <T n="text">0x5173D931<!--Each Horse can be <b>Purchased</b> for ยง1,000 or <b>Rescued</b> for ยง250. Due to the environment they came from, rescue Horses will have more difficult Traits, and extra attention and care may be needed.\n\nTo <b>Purchase</b> or <b>Rescue</b> a Horse visit the Phone's Home menu and select <b>Call Ranch Animal Exchange</b>, go to a Computer's Household category, use the <b>Ranch Community Board</b>, or visit the <b>Equestrian Center</b> in Chestnut Ridge's New Appaloosa Neighborhood.--></T>
    </U>
    <U>
      <T n="image" p="InEP14\UI\Lessons\EP14_HorseBuyRescueSell_Slide3.png">2f7d0004:00000000:dd7cd6c2785f3f17</T>
      <T n="text">0x6E6B2415<!--Horses can also be <b>Sold</b> for Simoleons. A Horse's value depends on their Skill Levels, past Competition Performance, quality of care, and age. If a Horse has <b>Champion Genes</b> this will also increase their value. Selling Horses is a great way to earn a healthy income... if you have quality Horses to back that ambition up.\n\nTo <b>Sell</b> a Horse visit the Phone's Home menu and select <b>Call Ranch Animal Exchange</b>, go to a Computer's Household category, use the <b>Ranch Community Board</b>, or visit the <b>Equestrian Center</b> in Chestnut Ridge's New Appaloosa Neighborhood.--></T>
    </U>
  </L>
